Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.11,0:00:09.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,This video is supported by Omaze, click the link below for a chance to win two seats on board one of Virgin Galactic's first flights into space!
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.80,0:00:14.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,自人类航天起步以来 只有大约六百人见过这番景象
Dialogue: 2,0:00:09.80,0:00:14.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since the beginning of spaceflight, only around 600 people have seen this view.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:15.14,0:00:19.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空一直是只有极少部分人才能去的地方
Dialogue: 2,0:00:15.14,0:00:19.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,Space has always been a place reserved for a tiny portion of the population.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:19.88,0:00:24.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,成为宇航员 往往要付出一生的努力
Dialogue: 2,0:00:19.88,0:00:24.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Being an astronaut is something that would usually require a lifetime of commitment.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:24.06,0:00:28.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,先要在学校选对专业 然后成为一名经验丰富的飞行员
Dialogue: 2,0:00:24.06,0:00:28.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,From taking the right subjects at school, getting flight experience as a pilot -
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.26,0:00:31.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,最终才能被宇航局招入麾下
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.26,0:00:31.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,to finally being accepted into a space agency.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.76,0:00:35.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,属实是花钱都换不来的东西
Dialogue: 2,0:00:31.76,0:00:35.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's one of the few things in life that even money couldn't buy.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:36.16,0:00:39.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,但现在 “宇航员”的定义渐渐有了改变
Dialogue: 2,0:00:36.16,0:00:39.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,But now the definition of 'astronaut' is starting to change.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:40.01,0:00:42.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,一般来讲 “宇航员”这个词的含义是
Dialogue: 2,0:00:40.01,0:00:42.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,For most of its existence, this word actually meant
Dialogue: 1,0:00:42.69,0:00:45.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,“为太空飞行而进行过训练的人”
Dialogue: 2,0:00:42.69,0:00:45.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,someone who had been trained to travel in a spacecraft.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:45.94,0:00:51.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以如果你没去过太空 但通过了一切所需的训练
Dialogue: 2,0:00:45.94,0:00:51.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,So even if you hadn't actually gone into space but passed all of the necessary training,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:51.25,0:00:53.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,那你也是一名宇航员
Dialogue: 2,0:00:51.25,0:00:53.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,you were technically an astronaut.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:53.94,0:00:56.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,但随着太空旅行产业伊始
Dialogue: 2,0:00:53.94,0:00:56.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,But now with the beginning of space tourism,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:56.39,0:01:00.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,对上太空的人的需求已经完全改变了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:56.39,0:01:00.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,the requirements for people travelling to space have completely flipped.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:00.75,0:01:05.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,那些登上维珍银河或者蓝色起源飞船的人
Dialogue: 2,0:01:00.75,0:01:05.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,Those wishing to hop on board either Virgin Galactic or Blue Origin's space vehicles
Dialogue: 1,0:01:05.67,0:01:10.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,几乎不用经过训练 但必须要有钞能力
Dialogue: 2,0:01:05.67,0:01:10.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,will require almost no training, but they will require a lot of money.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:11.37,0:01:17.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,尽管如此 还是有上百人已经订购了船票想要体验一把太空人的感觉
Dialogue: 2,0:01:11.37,0:01:17.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Despite this, hundreds of people have already bought tickets for the experience to become astronauts.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:17.69,0:01:22.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这和之前那些去过太空的有钱人有什么区别呢？
Dialogue: 2,0:01:17.69,0:01:22.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,But how is this any different from the other millionaires that have paid their way into space?
Dialogue: 1,0:01:23.43,0:01:26.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,2001年 美国企业家Dennis Tito
Dialogue: 2,0:01:23.43,0:01:26.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,In 2001, American entrepreneur Dennis Tito
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.79,0:01:32.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,花了2000万美元去国际空间站进行了一次8天的旅行
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.79,0:01:32.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,paid $20 million for an 8-day trip to the International Space Station.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:32.00,0:01:36.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,当时NASA认为让游客进太空不太好
Dialogue: 2,0:01:32.00,0:01:36.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,At the time, NASA thought it was inappropriate for tourists to go to space,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:36.49,0:01:38.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以拒绝训练他
Dialogue: 2,0:01:36.49,0:01:38.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,so they refused to train him.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:38.32,0:01:45.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以活让毛子接了 他和两名毛子宇航员搭乘联盟飞船TM32任务前往太空
Dialogue: 2,0:01:38.32,0:01:45.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,Instead, he partnered with the Russian's and took a ride on Soyuz mission TM32 along with two Cosmonauts.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:45.91,0:01:50.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,从那以后 就开始有很多百万富翁花钱上飞船
Dialogue: 2,0:01:45.91,0:01:50.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since then, various millionaires have paid for rides onboard space vehicles.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.90,0:01:52.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,但时代变了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.90,0:01:52.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,But things are changing.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:52.54,0:01:56.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空旅行脱离了政府公家的航天局
Dialogue: 2,0:01:52.54,0:01:56.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,Space tourists are now moving away from the typical government space agencies
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.78,0:01:58.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,转而向民营企业靠拢
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.78,0:01:58.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,and partnering with private companies.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:59.12,0:02:02.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了让太空旅行这个产业能做大做好
Dialogue: 2,0:01:59.12,0:02:02.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order for space tourism to become a thriving industry,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.43,0:02:05.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,企业需要拉低订票门槛 让普通人无需任何训练就能上船
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.43,0:02:05.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,it needs to be as easy as booking a plane ticket - without the need for any training.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.51,0:02:09.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,但民营企业又不能随便把人射到太空
Dialogue: 2,0:02:05.51,0:02:09.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,But a company can't just launch people into space without permission.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:09.53,0:02:14.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,就像民航飞机一样 所有飞船也要经过FAA许可
Dialogue: 2,0:02:09.53,0:02:14.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,Just like traditional aircraft, each vehicle needs to be approved by the FAA,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.48,0:02:17.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,才能运载大众旅客
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.48,0:02:17.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,in order for it to start flying regular passengers.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:17.69,0:02:21.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,FAA管的挺宽 从传统民航 到商业航天旅行都归他们
Dialogue: 2,0:02:17.69,0:02:21.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,The FAA is in charge of regulating all aspects of aviation,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.35,0:02:25.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,FAA管的挺宽 从传统民航 到商业航天旅行都归他们
Dialogue: 2,0:02:21.35,0:02:25.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,from traditional passenger airlines to commercial space travel.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:25.30,0:02:28.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为上太空的飞船一定会经过民航会用的空域
Dialogue: 2,0:02:25.30,0:02:28.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since space vehicles share the same airspace as airliners,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:28.81,0:02:33.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,FAA要负责让区域净空 保护老百姓
Dialogue: 2,0:02:28.81,0:02:33.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,the FAA is responsible for making sure everything is carried out safely and that the public are protected.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.61,0:02:37.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,但FAA在航空旅行和太空旅行上的管理却有很多不同
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.61,0:02:37.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the FAA's involvement with air travel is very different to space travel.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:43.49,0:02:49.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,从数量上看 FAA每年要管1650万架次的飞行
Dialogue: 2,0:02:43.49,0:02:49.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,To put it into perspective, the FAA handles around 16 and a half million flights per year.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:49.81,0:02:55.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,但放到航天领域 今年一共发射次数大概只有50
Dialogue: 2,0:02:49.81,0:02:55.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the space world, the number of launches expected to take place this year is around 50.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:55.66,0:03:01.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,但现在 太空旅行越来越多 发射数量也会急剧增长
Dialogue: 2,0:02:55.66,0:03:01.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,But now that space tourism is becoming a real thing, this number will start to grow rapidly.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.59,0:03:07.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,更不要说太空叉在搞的Starship亚轨道旅行了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.59,0:03:07.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,Not to mention SpaceX's grand plan for suborbital passenger travel using their Starship rocket.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:07.80,0:03:11.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们要在全球各地搞海上发射台
Dialogue: 2,0:03:07.80,0:03:11.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,They want to operate offshore launch platforms all around the globe
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.42,0:03:14.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,每天运送上千名旅客
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.42,0:03:14.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,with thousands of passengers travelling each day.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.42,0:03:18.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,以当前FAA的规章 这是完全不可能的
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.42,0:03:18.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,With the FAA's current rules, this would be impossible.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.81,0:03:23.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,美国企业在全球任何地方发射火箭都需要FAA许可
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.81,0:03:23.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you're an American entity launching a rocket anywhere in the world, you need an FAA license.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.20,0:03:27.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,但获取许可这件事是要花时间的
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.20,0:03:27.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,But getting a license isn't a quick process.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:27.70,0:03:33.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,公司提交申请文件 FAA要花上半年去审查
Dialogue: 2,0:03:27.70,0:03:33.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once a company files an application, it can take the FAA up to 180 days to review it.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:33.76,0:03:38.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,整个流程包含大量的测试与认证工作 全部完成后才能放行
Dialogue: 2,0:03:33.76,0:03:38.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,This process involves a huge amount of testing and verification before they can give the all clear.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:39.03,0:03:42.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,整个手续包含四款不同的规章条例
Dialogue: 2,0:03:39.03,0:03:42.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,The assessment is broken down into 4 different regulatory parts,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.62,0:03:45.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,每款都有一系列严格的安全需求
Dialogue: 2,0:03:42.62,0:03:45.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,each with their own set of strict safety requirements.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.26,0:03:49.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,火箭要有发射中止系统
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.26,0:03:49.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,The rocket needs to have a flight termination system,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:49.17,0:03:52.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,可以在火箭偏离预定路线后自毁
Dialogue: 2,0:03:49.17,0:03:52.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,which will purposefully blow up the rocket if it goes off course.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:52.89,0:03:59.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,让火箭从一个装满燃料的二踢脚炸碎成无数更细小的碎片
Dialogue: 2,0:03:52.89,0:03:59.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,This turns the rocket into much smaller pieces of debris rather than one enormous tank full of fuel.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:59.80,0:04:04.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果你想建一个太空港 FAA还会做一系列的环境方面的审查
Dialogue: 2,0:03:59.80,0:04:04.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order to operate a spaceport, the FAA also needs to do intense environmental checks
Dialogue: 1,0:04:04.93,0:04:09.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,确保火箭发射不会影响当地野生动物
Dialogue: 2,0:04:04.93,0:04:09.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,to make sure rocket launches won't destroy or disrupt any nearby wildlife.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.76,0:04:15.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,许可发下来 也要求必须是指定火箭从指定地点发射
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.76,0:04:15.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even if a license is granted, it only covers that particular rocket for that specific location,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.17,0:04:19.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,假设该火箭在所有发射中都遵循类似的轨迹
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.17,0:04:19.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,assuming that the rocket will follow a similar trajectory for all of its launches.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:20.17,0:04:24.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果火箭要换个地方发射 就要重新申请许可
Dialogue: 2,0:04:20.17,0:04:24.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,If a rocket is to be launched from a different location, a new license is needed.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:24.75,0:04:26.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,所有这一切都要花费大量时间——
Dialogue: 2,0:04:24.75,0:04:26.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,All of this takes a lot of time -
Dialogue: 1,0:04:26.85,0:04:30.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,而随着民营航天企业的飞速成长
Dialogue: 2,0:04:26.85,0:04:30.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,and as private space companies continue to make huge advancements,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:30.86,0:04:33.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,FAA的规章制度已经显得落后了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:30.86,0:04:33.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,the FAA is starting to fall behind.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:34.36,0:04:38.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,这点从太空叉最近的几次Starship测试中就能看出
Dialogue: 2,0:04:34.36,0:04:38.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,This became very evident with SpaceX's recent Starship tests.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:38.50,0:04:44.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,2020年12月 太空叉尝试发射Starship原型机并让其着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:04:38.50,0:04:44.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,In December 2020, SpaceX were attempting to launch and land their first ever Starship prototype.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:44.96,0:04:48.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,FAA和太空叉交涉过 并给了他们发射许可
Dialogue: 2,0:04:44.96,0:04:48.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,The FAA had worked with SpaceX and granted them a launch license,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:49.07,0:04:52.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,但他们只能在一定的天气条件下发射
Dialogue: 2,0:04:49.07,0:04:52.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,but they could only launch under certain weather conditions.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.51,0:04:58.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,在SN8上天几分钟前 FAA告知太空叉取消发射
Dialogue: 2,0:04:52.51,0:04:58.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,Just minutes before SN8 took off, the FAA told SpaceX to cancel the launch.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:58.81,0:05:02.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,而太空叉在任务控制中心的员工无视了这条消息
Dialogue: 2,0:04:58.81,0:05:02.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,SpaceX employees at mission control ignored this message,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.21,0:05:07.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为他们认为天气良好 FAA的监察员只是没有拿到最新的气象数据
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.21,0:05:07.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,since they thought the weather was fine and that the FAA inspector didn't have the latest weather data.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:14.49,0:05:20.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,那次震撼的发射后 SN8重着陆后发生爆炸
Dialogue: 2,0:05:14.49,0:05:20.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,After an impressive launch, SN8 had a hard landing and ended in a massive explosion.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:20.51,0:05:25.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然没人受伤 但FAA因为太空叉无视了自己的命令而表示I'm angry
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.51,0:05:25.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Although no one was injured, the FAA were angry that SpaceX had ignored their launch requirements.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:26.05,0:05:30.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,还启动了对太空叉的调查 不过最后他们也没损失什么
Dialogue: 2,0:05:26.05,0:05:30.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,This prompted an investigation into SpaceX but ultimately never cost them much,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:30.85,0:05:35.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,FAA也同意后续的Starship发射了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:30.85,0:05:35.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,as the FAA were happy for them to launch several other Starship's after this.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:35.51,0:05:42.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,不过FAA的确规定以后博卡奇卡发射Starship时必须有一名监察员在场
Dialogue: 2,0:05:35.51,0:05:42.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,They did however stipulate that an FAA inspector must be present for every flight of Starship from Boca Chica.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:43.24,0:05:46.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,这导致了SN11发射的推迟
Dialogue: 2,0:05:43.24,0:05:46.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,This led to the launch of SN11 being delayed
Dialogue: 1,0:05:46.26,0:05:50.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为FAA的监察员咕咕咕了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:46.26,0:05:50.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,because the FAA inspector couldn't make it down to Boca Chica in time.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:50.91,0:05:56.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉未经许可开始建造发射架时又和FAA打起来了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:50.91,0:05:56.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,SpaceX clashed with the FAA again when it started building a launch tower without permission.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:56.52,0:06:03.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个150米高的塔式结构将用于吊装巨大的Starship组件
Dialogue: 2,0:05:56.52,0:06:03.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,This 150 meter tall structure will one day lift and catch enormous Starship sections.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:03.66,0:06:08.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,在太空叉的赶工下 这个建筑盖得飞快
Dialogue: 2,0:06:03.66,0:06:08.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,The structure itself went up extremely quickly, with the usual SpaceX urgency.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:08.63,0:06:13.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,但FAA警告太空叉说 环境审查完成后 这个塔可能要大改
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.63,0:06:13.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the FAA warned SpaceX that it might need to drastically change the tower
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.10,0:06:15.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,但FAA警告太空叉说 环境审查完成后 这个塔可能要大改
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.10,0:06:15.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,once the environmental review is complete.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:16.00,0:06:22.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,太空叉说我不听我不听 还是加班加点修塔 修周边设施
Dialogue: 2,0:06:16.00,0:06:22.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Despite this, SpaceX continues to build the tower and the surrounding infrastructure at an incredible pace.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.24,0:06:24.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,在快速变化的发射计划下
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.24,0:06:24.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,With a rapid and ever changing launch schedule,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:24.92,0:06:28.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些规章制度严重阻碍了太空叉的发展
Dialogue: 2,0:06:24.92,0:06:28.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,these kinds of requirements stand in the way of SpaceX's progress.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:28.94,0:06:32.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,马一龙认为这放到以后是个大问题
Dialogue: 2,0:06:28.94,0:06:32.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,Elon Musk sees this as a big issue for the future.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:32.19,0:06:36.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,他认为FAA的规章都过时了 放过去可能说得通
Dialogue: 2,0:06:32.19,0:06:36.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,He claims that the FAA's rules are outdated and only made sense in the past,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:36.90,0:06:39.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为在以前 一年的发射也没几次
Dialogue: 2,0:06:36.90,0:06:39.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,when there were only a handful of rocket launches every year.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:40.29,0:06:43.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,大家都承认FAA在航空业的贡献
Dialogue: 2,0:06:40.29,0:06:43.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,No one is arguing that the FAA isn't a great thing for airplanes.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:44.02,0:06:48.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,但如果我们每天全世界有上百发火箭发射的话
Dialogue: 2,0:06:44.02,0:06:48.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if we want to have hundreds of rockets launching and landing each day around the world,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:48.35,0:06:52.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,那FAA就必须对他们的运行模式进行改革
Dialogue: 2,0:06:48.35,0:06:52.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,the FAA will need to drastically improve the way it operates.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:52.79,0:06:54.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,而FAA也的确在行动
Dialogue: 2,0:06:52.79,0:06:54.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that's exactly what it's doing.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:55.11,0:06:57.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了赶上创新的步伐
Dialogue: 2,0:06:55.11,0:06:57.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order to catch up with the pace of innovation,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:57.86,0:07:02.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,FAA正在努力简化航天公司的手续
Dialogue: 2,0:06:57.86,0:07:02.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,the FAA is now working to streamline the process for space companies.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:02.32,0:07:06.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,那四款规章条例现在已经被简化为一款
Dialogue: 2,0:07:02.32,0:07:06.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Those 4 parts of the rule book have now been condensed down into a single part
Dialogue: 1,0:07:06.46,0:07:08.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,适用于所有商业航天飞行活动
Dialogue: 2,0:07:06.46,0:07:08.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,for all commercial spaceflight.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:08.66,0:07:12.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,航天公司现在可以申请航天器运营商许可证
Dialogue: 2,0:07:08.66,0:07:12.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Space companies can now apply for a vehicle operator license,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.04,0:07:16.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,拿着这一个许可 就能从多个发射场发射火箭了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:12.04,0:07:16.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,which will allow them to fly from multiple different launch sites under the same license.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:17.01,0:07:21.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果太空叉想做亚轨道旅行项目的话 那这个许可至关重要
Dialogue: 2,0:07:17.01,0:07:21.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,This will be crucial if SpaceX are to go ahead with their Earth to Earth travel idea.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:21.89,0:07:25.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然坐Starship旅行这件事看起来还很遥远
Dialogue: 2,0:07:21.89,0:07:25.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Although the idea of Starship Earth travel may seem far away,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:25.21,0:07:29.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,但类似的亚轨道旅行却已经实现了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:25.21,0:07:29.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,the same kind of suborbital passenger travel is already happening.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:29.97,0:07:35.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,维珍银河和蓝色起源都成功送乘客进入了太空
Dialogue: 2,0:07:29.97,0:07:35.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Virgin Galactic and Blue Origin have now achieved their goals of flying passengers to space.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.75,0:07:42.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,经过近20年的努力 两家公司竟然在同一个月达成了这个目标
Dialogue: 2,0:07:35.75,0:07:42.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,After trying for nearly two decades, amazingly, both companies achieved this goal in the exact same month.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:42.59,0:07:47.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,但他们也和太空叉一样要面对FAA这一硬茬
Dialogue: 2,0:07:42.59,0:07:47.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,But the FAA was just as much of a hurdle to them as it was for SpaceX.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:47.42,0:07:53.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,最开始 维珍银河的许可只包含了专业飞行员和宇航员的测试飞行
Dialogue: 2,0:07:47.42,0:07:53.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,Initially, Virgin Galactic's license only covered test flights with professional pilots and astronauts.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:53.71,0:07:58.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,不过最近他们把许可更新为了完整的商业发射许可
Dialogue: 2,0:07:53.71,0:07:58.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, this license was recently updated to a full commercial launch license,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:58.21,0:08:00.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,可以带乘客飞了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:58.21,0:08:00.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,allowing them to start flying passengers.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:00.86,0:08:05.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,这对于那些已经买了票打算上太空的六百来人是个好消息
Dialogue: 2,0:08:00.86,0:08:05.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,This was good news for the 600 people that have already bought tickets for a ride into space.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:06.21,0:08:11.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,FAA要求他们在正式开始前再做两次额外的测试飞行
Dialogue: 2,0:08:06.21,0:08:11.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,The FAA requires them to do two additional test flights before they can start doing their own thing.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:11.87,0:08:17.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,一旦之后的测试飞行圆满完成 那你们的机会就来了！
Dialogue: 2,0:08:11.87,0:08:17.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once the remaining test flights have been completed successfully, it could be your chance to go to space.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:18.10,0:08:24.71,辉中,,0,0,0,,猝不及防的工商时间……
Dialogue: 2,0:08:18.10,0:08:24.71,辉英,,0,0,0,,Omaze is giving away two free seats on one of the first Virgin Galactic flights to Space!
Dialogue: 1,0:08:24.95,0:08:30.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,In the history of humanity, just 600 people have been into space and now you could be one of them.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:31.34,0:08:37.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,During the flight, you and your guest will experience weightlessness as you hover above our planet at 80km,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:37.88,0:08:40.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,with a view like never before.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:40.45,0:08:46.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,And if going to space wasn't enough for you, you'll also get a VIP tour of Spaceport America,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:46.78,0:08:50.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,the incredible facility from which your journey will begin.
